---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About this archive.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      Some things are worth keeping. Not because they're yours, but because they
      once changed the temperature of a room you were standing in, and you wanted
      to keep standing there.
    </p>
    <p>
      John &amp; Mario is a personal archive of those things. It began as a Tumblr
      between 2011 and 2013 — a wall of images collected with no system beyond
      <em>this one, yes</em>. It's being rebuilt here, on infrastructure I own, with
      no feed to feed and no one to perform for.
    </p>
    <p>
      There are two ways in. <strong>Look</strong> is for images — the original
      impulse, mostly other people's photographs, kept for the way they hold light
      or hold still. <strong>Read</strong> is for words — lines worth carrying
      around, set in the type they deserve. More rooms may open later. The house
      stays the same.
    </p>
    <p>
      A confession about the images: they are mostly not mine. They were gathered
      over years, long before I thought to write down where anything came from. I
      don't claim them. Where I know the source, it's credited. Where I don't, I'd
      genuinely like to — if you recognise something, tell me, and I'll add the
      credit or take it down, gladly.
    </p>
    <p>
      That's the whole arrangement. No comments, no likes, no metrics quietly
      counting you. Just a place to keep the things that seemed worth keeping, in
      case they're worth keeping to you too.
    </p>
    {CONTACT_EMAIL && (
      <p><a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a></p>
    )}
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
